      "role": "user",
      "content": "but how are those \"small actions\" supposed to matter when the scale of the disaster is so massive? it feels like just rearranging deck chairs on the titanic. if everything is just going to burn or drown anyway, it feels so irrational to go through all the effort of working, studying, and struggling for a future that literally isn't going to exist. it just feels like a slow, painful waste of time.",
