      "content": "That frustration is valid when the scale of global crises seems absolute, but choosing to be present often offers a rare form of resistance against a world that feels chaotic and indifferent to us. Thinking about how your very actions might contribute to positive developments, even in the delay, rather than pretending that the world is safe, can help find a more constructive path. Many people find meaning by accepting that they cannot control the entire ship while still building their own seat, understanding that the meaning of life isn't always to prevent disasters but to witness and participate in them with some purpose.",
